values:
Well, Josh came on Saturday as planned but he managed to get the stomach flu or food poisoning. He was sick all day which ruined most&nbsp;to all of our plans but we did a bit of talking and watching my siblings wrestle for sticks and staves.&nbsp;My mom managed to convince his mom&nbsp;to let him stay the night and catch the bus tomorrow because he started to run a fever before he left on the strain. Since he wasn't retaining any liquids to&nbsp;regulate him temperature and he was going to be on the train&nbsp;for 12 hours,&nbsp;I was a little reluctant to let him go. He is currently still&nbsp;sleeping but he seems to be feeling much better to my relief. He will leave sometime around 11&nbsp;am or&nbsp;6&nbsp;pm depending on how he's feeling.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

I have to admit, it was really hard to see him in that state. 

Otherwise, I start school tomorrow and my first period doesn't start yet!!! Not until September. Go college classes!!! woot woot!

Well, I have now officially started the new semester. I have 3 new classes and a&nbsp;one&nbsp;course that lasts the whole year. I am currently in my&nbsp;Honors World History. We are in the computer lab that&nbsp;apparently&nbsp; has internet. This&nbsp;new semester is going to be rather interesting I can tell. I have almost everyone from my Honors English class and AVID class in my Honors, Health, and AVID class this semester. These people are going to be in most of my highschool life. 

I have new friend now. Her name is Mickell and oddly enough, she is my best friend Brock's sweetheart. Despite not having met eachother in person, we're already asking eachother for advice and talking about matters of the heart. This friendship reminds me a lot of my friendship with Becky but Mickell is a LOT closer and Brock knows her because she lives near his dad's house. Hopefully I will find the time and the transportation method to go down to Elk Grove to visit her. I have my doubts about whether or not this will happen any time soon but hey, hope for the best expect the worst right?&nbsp;

Unfortunately, my friends seem to expect the worst. Lately, I have been having some stomach trouble. I cannot eat a lot because my stomach can't handle it and sometimes... rejects the food. I also have a heightened sense of smell and taste. I can now taste and smell things I would not have regularly noticed, and most of it is unpleasant. Apparently, this adds up to being pregnant. My friends all assume that I am pregnant and I am not even sexually active! My dear friend Zach said that he will either knee me in the stomach or feed me seaweed to make me have a miscarriage if I am pregnant. That kind of upsets me because he would basically be murdering my child and that is not a pleasant thought. This is also the THIRD time someone has assumed I am pregnant because of a malfunction of a body part or pain in a specific area, such as my abdomen. It is getting rather irritating.

I have become sick once again. That is two throat infections in less than a month. This is really becoming&nbsp;irritating, quite literally. I can no more&nbsp;breath as I&nbsp;can swallow without pain, it really sucks. And apparently, not medication is going to help. I have been&nbsp; pumping myself full of drugs to get rid of the pain for that last two days and nothing helps. That is just plain rediculous.&nbsp;

Another bit of information that boggled me out of my mind. My good friend Angelique has been engaged for about 2 months or so, but the first couple of weeks she had absolutely no idea who it was that she was engaged to. All she knew was that is was the brother or cousing of her ex. Well, she met him finally and I kept hearing about him and on Thursday I got to meet him. It was my friend Ben from the 8th grade. "WHAT THE-" was my initial reaction. I asked him why he was at my school and told me that his girlfriend went here. Well, when I found out I nearly lost it because it was just so weird. Here was the play boy who was never serious about girls and treated them badly, also the guy that used to dip and kiss me while I was dating my ex Johnny. (just a kiss on the cheek but I basically stayed in the shower for an hour scrubbing the area in which he had kissed me.)&nbsp;

It seems that someone chose to make my fate a little interesting by re-introducing people from my past years in middle-school into my highschool years. He is not the first person this year, my friend Zach also came this year. These were all friends from the 7th and 8th grade that I NEVER thought I was going to see again and here they are. Life is so weird. Well, there's my little bit of highschool drama for the day.

Today on the way home a couple of kids i knew were fighting a boy. When they got around the corner they said that they would all&nbsp;jump him as soon as he got around the corner on the bike. Once the kid got next to them all three started to move in to fight him a freakin 3-1 FIGHT! I LOST it soooo badly.&nbsp; 

I started to yell at all three of them fully enraged. I told the three boys to back the heck&nbsp;up from&nbsp;him and yelled&nbsp;at the boy and told him to get on his bike and leave. When the&nbsp;three boys tried to&nbsp;hit him again&nbsp;I kicked on of them and almost&nbsp;punched the other two in the jaw and one of them was only about 8-10 years old, the other two boys&nbsp;are friends of my sisters and are abou 13-14 years old.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

But i didn't say heck or anything even slightly nice. I used profanity to the extreme. I used it like it should never be used. I can't even give the slightest detail at how angry i was. Just imagine the worst situation where someone was truly angry at you and times that by&nbsp;5 or 10. Thats how angry i was. 

When the boy left i, still fully&nbsp;enraged, told them that if they ever try to jump a kid in front of me again, and they TOLD me that they were going to, i wasn't butting my nose in some one elses business, &nbsp;i would&nbsp;beat all three of them up and not give a&nbsp;dang what happened.&nbsp;I not only scared myself with how angry i had gotten, since i haven't gotten that angry in YEARS, but i also scared my friend Zach, who has never seen me so angry. I quite honestly think that no one i have known in that last 3 years has ever seen me so angry. I felt kind of ashamed at how enraged i had gotten but i cannot and will not stand for injustice or unfairness, ESPECIALLY when you are going to fight some one. I wouldn't have cared if it was a one on one fight because then it would have been slightly fair, but jumping someone is NOT cool.&nbsp; 

When i got home and told my sister, she was truly angry at me since i had hit one of her friends, which she had every right to be. She didn't realize the reason behind it though, just that i hit her friend. Gah, i'm still a little angry from the whole encounter but i've managed to get a hold of my temper.
